  "explanation": "In determining the sentence, the court must balance the severity of the offense with the mitigating factors presented. Embezzlement by an accountant represents a severe breach of fiduciary duty and the trust placed in the defendant by their employer. White-collar crimes of this nature require a penalty that provides general deterrence to others in similar positions of financial trust. However, the court heavily considers that the defendant is a first-time offender with no prior criminal record. Furthermore, the defendant has already made efforts to partially repay the embezzled funds, which demonstrates remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. Taking these factors into account, a short term of incarceration is appropriate to reflect the seriousness of the offense, which will be followed by supervised release and a strict mandate to complete full restitution.",
